Global Non-metallic Electrical Fittings Market Insights
Non-metallic Electrical Fittings Market size was valued at USD 5.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 7.9 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.8% from 2024 to 2030.

Non-metallic Electrical Fittings Market Overview
The global Non-metallic Electrical Fittings Market is valued at USD 3.2 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 5.0 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% during the forecast period. This market includes products like junction boxes, conduit fittings, and connectors, typically made from materials like PVC, fiberglass, and other composites, which offer superior resistance to corrosion and electrical conductivity. With the growing demand for safety and energy-efficient solutions in the electrical industry, the market is seeing substantial growth, especially in residential and commercial applications. Non-metallic electrical fittings are also witnessing increasing demand due to their lightweight, cost-effectiveness, and ease of installation, offering a sustainable alternative to metallic fittings.

